1
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,270
I think it's time to blow this scene

2
00:00:10,270 --> 00:00:12,550
Get everybody and their stuff together

3
00:00:12,550 --> 00:00:14,990
Okay, three, two, one let's jam

4
00:01:43,540 --> 00:01:46,410
Come out! You can't run anymore!

5
00:01:46,410 --> 00:01:47,370
We'll shoot!

6
00:01:47,370 --> 00:01:49,790
Give up already, Abdul Hakim!

7
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:54,850
So ya wanna fight, huh?

8
00:01:54,850 --> 00:01:55,920
You're such a...

9
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,510
<i>Amigo!</i>

10
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:52,140
<i>How're all you 300,000 bounty hunters</i>
<i>in the solar system doing?</i>

11
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:55,730
<i>It's time for Big Shot, the show that
brings you information about fugitives!</i>

12
00:02:55,730 --> 00:03:01,520
<i>Well, well, first up for today
is this guy: Abdul Hakim.</i>

13
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:04,870
<i>He's known as a serial pet thief.</i>

14
00:03:04,870 --> 00:03:08,620
<i>This time, he snagged a test animal from
a research facility, and is on the loose.</i>

15
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:13,350
<i>The good news is that he's
worth a whopping 8 million!</i>

16
00:03:13,350 --> 00:03:14,710
<i>The conditions are as always.</i>

17
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:17,670
<i>Bring him in alive to collect your reward.</i>

18
00:03:17,670 --> 00:03:19,550
<i>If you kill him,</i>
<i>kiss your reward good-bye.</i>

19
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:23,160
<i>He's the biggest we've had in a while.</i>
<i>Do your best to get this guy!</i>

20
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:24,510
How's it look?

21
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:26,270
It's done for.

22
00:03:26,270 --> 00:03:28,430
Man, why does everything...

23
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:31,450
<i>Hey!</i>

24
00:03:31,450 --> 00:03:33,430
Doctor? You got information?

25
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:35,150
<i>About Abdul Hakim.</i>

26
00:03:35,550 --> 00:03:36,360
<i>I'll take it!</i>

27
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,290
I'll give a discount. 300.

28
00:03:38,290 --> 00:03:40,450
I got his post-plastic surgery picture.

29
00:03:40,450 --> 00:03:42,010
<i>Too much. 20 down.</i>

30
00:03:42,010 --> 00:03:46,700
All right, 280. On one condition.

31
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:47,850
What's that?

32
00:03:47,850 --> 00:03:49,410
<i>Sock him one.</i>

33
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:54,880
<i>He trampled over me. If you want,
punch him a dozen times.</i>

34
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:21,040
I've got the goods.

35
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:23,550
This one should be something big...

36
00:04:24,150 --> 00:04:26,150
Yeah, see you in six hours.

37
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:29,980
<i>He had a very conspicuous suitcase.</i>

38
00:04:29,980 --> 00:04:31,920
That info's included in the deal, right?

39
00:04:32,460 --> 00:04:34,000
<i>Oh, all right.</i>

40
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,350
<i>It was something that could</i>
<i>carry a small woman inside.</i>

41
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:38,650
Treasure?

42
00:04:38,650 --> 00:04:40,240
<i>Can't really say.</i>

43
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:42,880
<i>The way he handled it</i>
<i>sure didn't seem that way.</i>

44
00:04:52,860 --> 00:04:54,340
Ni-lai-la!

45
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:57,960
If you feel lethargic,
have some ginseng hei-sui.

46
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:59,820
You'll last a week with it!

47
00:04:59,820 --> 00:05:02,760
If you're tired, have sugarcane hei-sui.

48
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,530
You ate too much?
Then have pineapple hei-sui.

49
00:05:05,990 --> 00:05:07,420
Gimme some lao-chu.

50
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:08,030
Thank you.

51
00:05:08,030 --> 00:05:09,340
Here you go.

52
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,460
Oops! 

53
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:15,160
Sorry. My apologies, bro.

54
00:05:17,030 --> 00:05:19,400
Hey, I said I'm sorry!

55
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:21,500
What, can't say anything?

56
00:05:24,710 --> 00:05:27,050
Wh-What? Ya pickin' a fight?

57
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:30,720
My treat.

58
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:37,810
Drink.

59
00:06:02,210 --> 00:06:04,710
And now, the loot.

60
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:34,580
Even if I overhaul this whole craft,
I'll have some change!

61
00:06:34,980 --> 00:06:36,830
Guess I'll go eat Peking Duck with it.

62
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:40,710
As they say, "Don't count
chickens before they hatch." 

63
00:06:42,590 --> 00:06:44,060
I got this one nailed shut!

64
00:06:44,060 --> 00:06:45,920
<i>Well, give it what you got.</i>

65
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:56,880
So all three went down?

66
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:58,210
Seems that way.

67
00:06:58,210 --> 00:07:00,120
And Hakim is around here?

68
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,040
Seems that way.

69
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:04,110
Dammit, he doesn't even
know its true value. 

70
00:07:04,790 --> 00:07:06,320
A pet shop?

71
00:07:06,890 --> 00:07:09,030
A shady one at that.

72
00:07:09,530 --> 00:07:14,970
Hey, bro, you can buy anything here on Mars.

73
00:07:14,970 --> 00:07:18,200
From guns to human lives.

74
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,960
If ya wanna know, show me what ya got.

75
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:23,460
The chain on this one is long.
Must be the "Way of the Dragon" model. 

76
00:07:23,460 --> 00:07:27,340
Oh, you can tell?
That's a rare one from the '30s!

77
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:30,220
It sure is an antique.

78
00:07:30,930 --> 00:07:35,780
Try the store called Animal Treasure
off of Caiphon Road.

79
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:37,630
I'm sure you'll find something there.

80
00:07:42,950 --> 00:07:47,000
Okay, I'll look... but I'll decide if I
want to buy it from you after I see it.

81
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,400
Oh, all right.

82
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:05,180
Run out of funds changing your
face around too much, Hakim?

83
00:08:05,180 --> 00:08:06,590
W-Wait a sec...

84
00:08:06,590 --> 00:08:08,010
Hey, don't move.

85
00:08:08,010 --> 00:08:11,830
You sure are restless, changing
your face around this much.

86
00:08:11,830 --> 00:08:12,550
What the—?

87
00:08:12,550 --> 00:08:15,690
Hold it. I don't want any
of this business here.

88
00:08:15,690 --> 00:08:17,670
All of my babies are very sensitive!

89
00:08:17,670 --> 00:08:19,160
You open it.

90
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,390
Why me?! 

91
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,140
This is all a misunderstanding... 

92
00:08:22,140 --> 00:08:23,020
Hurry it up!

93
00:08:28,020 --> 00:08:29,230
Oh, fine.

94
00:08:41,850 --> 00:08:43,130
Oh!

95
00:08:45,610 --> 00:08:46,460
A dog?

96
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:50,050
A Welsh Corgi. It's cute, but it's everywhere.

97
00:08:50,050 --> 00:08:52,260
Not a particularly rare species.

98
00:08:52,260 --> 00:08:54,630
And how much is it worth?

99
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:57,580
With the suitcase, about this much.

100
00:08:57,580 --> 00:08:58,520
200K?

101
00:08:58,520 --> 00:08:59,720
No, no, 200, 200!

102
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,220
No way!

103
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:04,570
You don't like it, you take care
of it yourself. Like eating it.

104
00:09:04,570 --> 00:09:06,190
It <i>is</i> a puppy...

105
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:09,040
Sorry to bother you. Please continue.

106
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:19,370
I guess the Peking Duck
has been overcooked.

107
00:09:19,780 --> 00:09:21,350
At least give me 300...

108
00:09:21,350 --> 00:09:22,450
No can do.

109
00:09:22,450 --> 00:09:23,340
280?

110
00:09:23,340 --> 00:09:24,460
A no is a no.

111
00:09:24,460 --> 00:09:25,880
250!

112
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:28,170
Zero. I'll take it back.

113
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:30,920
This again? What is it this time?

114
00:09:40,610 --> 00:09:44,480
Someone! Catch my babies! Hurry! 

115
00:09:42,970 --> 00:09:43,850
{\an8}There it is!

116
00:09:43,850 --> 00:09:44,480
{\an8}All right!

117
00:09:50,860 --> 00:09:52,130
Hakim?!

118
00:09:52,130 --> 00:09:54,320
God dammit, what's going on?!

119
00:10:36,060 --> 00:10:37,990
Gangway!

120
00:10:36,690 --> 00:10:37,990
{\an8}What the hell?

121
00:10:38,350 --> 00:10:39,700
Wait, dammit! 

122
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:42,590
Hey, what the hell do you want?!

123
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:57,330
Bounty hunter?

124
00:10:57,330 --> 00:10:59,300
Animal rights syndicate?

125
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:01,750
Your story brings a tear to my eye.

126
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:04,350
Risking your life on a dog
that's only worth 200 woolongs.

127
00:11:04,350 --> 00:11:05,430
What?

128
00:11:05,430 --> 00:11:10,560
What I want are the 8 million woolongs
hanging from <i>your</i> neck.

129
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:23,910
Not bad.

130
00:11:25,030 --> 00:11:25,870
What?!

131
00:11:27,290 --> 00:11:27,950
Dammit!

132
00:11:42,990 --> 00:11:46,100
Shuddup! I'm in a rotten mood right now!

133
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:03,490
There, there. Here, lemme put on a collar.

134
00:12:03,910 --> 00:12:06,040
A dog instead of a duck, huh?

135
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:09,010
Forget about that!
You know anything about it?

136
00:12:09,010 --> 00:12:13,670
Yeah. This is a Welsh Corgi.
A total mongrel.

137
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:14,920
Totally?

138
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:18,000
Totally. Completely worthless.

139
00:12:18,410 --> 00:12:21,310
Shit, this gives me a headache. 

140
00:12:21,310 --> 00:12:23,510
And all this is because of this mongrel—

141
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:30,470
The dog is worthless,
but the <i>owner</i> is worth something.

142
00:12:30,470 --> 00:12:33,270
Well, at least you should get
to know this critter well.

143
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:36,480
Man, I hate kids and critters!

144
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:38,650
They're nothing but trouble!

145
00:12:41,310 --> 00:12:42,040
I got something!

146
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:43,650
All right!

147
00:12:43,650 --> 00:12:44,710
It's big! 

148
00:12:44,710 --> 00:12:45,500
Here it comes!

149
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,630
Pull on the line!

150
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:53,580
What time is it now?

151
00:12:55,290 --> 00:12:57,420
I-I-It's 4 o'clock now.

152
00:12:58,340 --> 00:12:59,920
Two hours...

153
00:13:01,380 --> 00:13:04,880
Who was that with Hakim? His ally?

154
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:06,050
Seems that way.

155
00:13:06,730 --> 00:13:09,870
We got no clues?
We have to do something.

156
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:12,500
If <i>that</i> falls into police hands,
we're in deep shit.

157
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,640
Seems that way.

158
00:13:13,640 --> 00:13:17,360
All our work will be worthless if our
experiments get revealed to the public.

159
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,360
Seems that way.

160
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:21,860
How much does he think we
put into that "data dog"?

161
00:13:22,420 --> 00:13:24,900
Why don't <i>you</i> do this?

162
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:29,910
Didn't your grandma teach you
to finish what you start?

163
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:32,620
She was dead before I was born.

164
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:36,870
<i>Sorry to hear that. Anyway,
we have the joker in our hand.</i>

165
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:39,130
Just do what we planned.

166
00:13:39,130 --> 00:13:41,790
Give me code name "snoop."

167
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:46,930
Yeah. It's me. I had some trouble.

168
00:13:48,220 --> 00:13:50,410
No big deal...

169
00:13:50,930 --> 00:13:53,350
Hey, wait, Michael!

170
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:57,200
I want to postpone the meeting a bit.

171
00:13:57,870 --> 00:13:59,730
As I said, it wasn't that big a deal...

172
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:04,200
Impossible? Why? Hey, wait!

173
00:14:11,850 --> 00:14:14,040
And <i>this</i> is our plan?

174
00:14:18,060 --> 00:14:20,000
Hey, you!

175
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:23,000
You have something you
want to know, right?

176
00:14:23,620 --> 00:14:25,010
Wait!

177
00:14:25,010 --> 00:14:29,470
My little Peeko can answer your questions!

178
00:14:29,470 --> 00:14:32,680
You have something you
want to know, right?

179
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:36,180
See, little Peeko is telling me

180
00:14:36,180 --> 00:14:40,190
that you're looking for
someone or something.

181
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:48,700
Well, where there's this dog, there's Hakim.

182
00:14:49,380 --> 00:14:51,660
Seeing loud and clear.

183
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:54,120
We're counting on you, pooch.

184
00:14:54,990 --> 00:14:57,620
We must resort to the dog whistle.

185
00:14:57,620 --> 00:14:59,820
But that'll cause a big mess.

186
00:14:59,820 --> 00:15:00,770
I don't care.

187
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:02,230
We'll draw attention to ourselves! 

188
00:15:02,230 --> 00:15:03,630
We have no choice!

189
00:15:03,630 --> 00:15:05,080
Shall I?

190
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:05,920
Do it.

191
00:15:14,640 --> 00:15:16,170
I can't hear anything.

192
00:15:16,170 --> 00:15:18,730
I said before that humans can't hear it.

193
00:15:18,730 --> 00:15:20,690
Oh, that's right.

194
00:15:21,210 --> 00:15:24,170
This is so far fetched...

195
00:15:25,120 --> 00:15:27,810
Will this really attract?

196
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:36,950
Oh, it's moving. Something is
now on the move.

197
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:42,250
Wait! Babies, what's wrong with you guys?!

198
00:15:45,260 --> 00:15:46,340
Hey, wait!

199
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:53,390
It got away, Jet!

200
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:55,580
Huh? Hakim? 

201
00:15:55,580 --> 00:15:56,350
<i>No, the dog!</i> 

202
00:15:56,350 --> 00:16:00,850
It's close, it's close!
What you are looking for is nearby.

203
00:16:00,850 --> 00:16:04,230
In fact, right in front of your eyes... 

204
00:16:05,990 --> 00:16:07,980
Hey, wait, you need to pay!

205
00:16:07,980 --> 00:16:09,030
I'll pay when I'm rich! 

206
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:11,200
You can't be serious...

207
00:16:18,370 --> 00:16:20,750
Goddammit, what the hell is going on?!

208
00:16:26,710 --> 00:16:27,980
Happy?

209
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:29,600
Yes, very.

210
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:32,940
Excuse me... 

211
00:16:32,940 --> 00:16:33,800
Outta my way!

212
00:16:38,020 --> 00:16:40,180
You, what are you doing?

213
00:16:43,020 --> 00:16:43,810
Hakim!

214
00:16:52,780 --> 00:16:53,740
Dammit!

215
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:57,740
It's just a dog, after all.

216
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,000
Hakim!

217
00:17:06,050 --> 00:17:08,880
<i>Spike, he's headed for Interstate 6.</i>

218
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:12,090
<i>Great! If he thinks he can
outrun me, he's welcome to try!</i>

219
00:17:12,090 --> 00:17:13,880
Don't get too hotheaded!

220
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:16,050
What part of me is hotheaded?!

221
00:17:20,850 --> 00:17:21,810
There he is!

222
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:40,780
This is payback from earlier!

223
00:17:49,580 --> 00:17:52,340
The hell are you doin'?!
This guy is mine!

224
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:02,220
What the—?

225
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:03,220
Now!

226
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:07,060
Stop that! 

227
00:18:09,310 --> 00:18:10,480
S-Shit!

228
00:18:13,700 --> 00:18:14,360
Shit!

229
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:17,030
<i>This</i> is why I hate critters!

230
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,000
<i>Amigo!</i>

231
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,510
<i>How're all you 300,000 bounty hunters</i>
<i>in the solar system doing?</i>

232
00:18:43,510 --> 00:18:47,530
<i>It's time for Big Shot, the show that</i>
<i>brings you information about fugitives!</i>

233
00:18:47,530 --> 00:18:49,930
<i>So, you remember Abdul Hakim</i>
<i>who chose a rather</i>

234
00:18:49,930 --> 00:18:53,100
<i>flashy way of turning himself in last week?</i>

235
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:54,690
<i>Yeah! Of course!</i>

236
00:18:54,690 --> 00:18:59,310
<i>Apparently, he stole
what's called a "data dog"</i>

237
00:18:59,310 --> 00:19:02,160
<i>created in an illegal experiment
of some research firm.</i>

238
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:03,900
<i>Wow! What's that?</i>

239
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:08,940
<i>I'm not sure myself, but apparently</i>
<i>it's a very intelligent pooch.</i>

240
00:19:08,940 --> 00:19:12,580
<i>I hear that it's priceless among collectors.</i>

241
00:19:12,580 --> 00:19:17,460
<i>That's a surprise!</i>
<i>I wanna have a dog like that!</i>

242
00:19:17,460 --> 00:19:19,930
<i>But they say it's still missing.</i>

243
00:19:19,930 --> 00:19:22,130
<i>I wonder where it went?</i>

244
00:19:22,130 --> 00:19:25,240
<i>Really! But now, a commercial!</i>

245
00:19:27,150 --> 00:19:28,730
Can't be...

246
00:19:28,730 --> 00:19:33,480
Hey there! When you're done cleaning,
feed the komodo dragons!

247
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:36,020
I want you to work your ass off!

248
00:19:36,020 --> 00:19:37,200
Yeah...

249
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:41,240
Hey, hey!

250
00:19:44,030 --> 00:19:46,240
Hey, don't jump on there!

251
00:19:46,990 --> 00:19:48,080
That's cold!

252
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:52,850
That's why I said we should
throw out mongrels like this one!

253
00:19:52,850 --> 00:19:54,950
But you're the one that brought it here!

254
00:19:55,490 --> 00:19:58,170
In any case, we have to do
something about the ticks.

255
00:19:58,750 --> 00:20:00,420
Shit...

256
00:20:00,420 --> 00:20:02,430
I'm gonna salt you and eat you, dammit!

257
00:20:02,430 --> 00:20:05,260
<i>Well, it's time for us to go.</i>
<i>See you next time!</i>

258
00:20:05,260 --> 00:20:06,560
<i>Good luck!</i>

259
00:20:22,950 --> 00:20:28,250
<i>♪ Too much time has passed by ♪</i>

260
00:20:22,950 --> 00:20:28,250
{\an8}<i>♪ aishiteta to nageku niwa ♪</i>

261
00:20:28,250 --> 00:20:33,150
<i>♪ to lament that we were deeply in love ♪</i>

262
00:20:28,250 --> 00:20:33,150
{\an8}<i>♪ amarinimo toki wa sugite shimatta ♪</i>

263
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:40,250
<i>♪ The wind keeps blowing, while my heart ♪</i>

264
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:40,250
{\an8}<i>♪ mada kokoro no hokorobi wo ♪</i>

265
00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:44,840
<i>♪ cannot heal all the tears in it ♪</i>

266
00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:44,840
{\an8}<i>♪ iyasenu mama kaze ga fuiteru ♪</i>

267
00:20:46,890 --> 00:20:55,260
<i>♪ Someone, cry for me with parched eyes ♪</i>

268
00:20:46,890 --> 00:20:55,260
{\an8}<i>♪ kawaita hitomi de dareka naite kure ♪</i>

269
00:20:57,590 --> 00:21:01,150
<i>♪ The real folk blues ♪</i>

270
00:21:01,150 --> 00:21:09,620
<i>♪ I only want to know what true sadness is ♪</i>

271
00:21:01,150 --> 00:21:09,620
{\an8}<i>♪ honto no kanashimi ga shiritai dake ♪</i>

272
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:16,130
<i>♪ Sitting in muddy water ♪</i>

273
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:16,130
{\an8}<i>♪ doro no kawa ni tsukatta ♪</i>

274
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:21,720
<i>♪ isn't such a bad life ♪</i>

275
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:21,720
{\an8}<i>♪ jinsei mo waruku wa nai ♪</i>

276
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:30,400
<i>♪ if it ends after the first time ♪</i>

277
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:30,400
{\an8}<i>♪ ichido kiri de owaru nara ♪</i>

278
00:21:48,190 --> 00:21:51,620
"Nothing is permanent." It's a fact of life.

279
00:21:52,620 --> 00:21:54,660
The bell tolls for the great
ones who'll someday fall. 

280
00:21:54,660 --> 00:21:57,420
Money makes the world go round, 

281
00:21:58,130 --> 00:22:01,040
but debt piles up before you know it.

282
00:22:02,130 --> 00:22:04,790
I wandered through
all the reaches of space,

283
00:22:04,790 --> 00:22:07,430
and there I met a cowboy.

284
00:22:07,430 --> 00:22:12,560
A session to the tune of an off-key melody:

285
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:14,260
Honky Tonk Women.
